SUBENT        C3100004   20260113   20260312   20260312       C253
BIB                  5         28
REACTION   (7-N-14(P,G)8-O-15,PAR,DA)
METHOD     (GSPEC) The second setup, a HPGe clover detector,
           consisting of four 25% crystals, was positioned in
           close proximity to the target at an angle of 45
           degree with respect to the beam direction. The ground
           state is a complex mixture of direct and resonance
           capture components and the interferences between
           them. The experimental angular distribution can be
           described as Wexpt(theta)=a0*(1+Sum ai*Qi*Pi(cos
           theta)), where ai are the angular distribution
           coefficients and Qi are the attenuation factors due
           to the finite size of the detector. The Pi
            (cos theta) are the Legendre polynomials of order i.
           The Qi, which are geometric correction factors for
           the finite solid angle subtended by the detector.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical uncertainties.
           (ERR-SYS) Systematic uncertainty.
CORRECTION Angular attenuation coefficients used for solid angle
           corrections:
           Q-coeff    Value
           0          1
           1          0.7165
           2          0.3682
           3          0.0636
           4          -0.0977
STATUS     (TABLE,,Q.Li+,J,PR/C,93,055806,2016) Data were
           provided by R.J.deBoer on January 8, 2026.
           (COREL,C3100002) Data from angular distribution setup.
ENDBIB              28
